Art is simply nothing but a mess of colors or design of randomness. The phrase "art for art's sake" refers to allowing items to exist just because of what they have been declared to be. For example, to large populations, abstract art could be described as a simple pattern seen every day. To the experienced art collector/dealer, the abstract art could symbolize something beyond a simple everyday thing. From this, the piece of art should maintain its description of art for art's sake.